## On Gate Failure

If a gate transition from this stage fails, a `.gate-feedback.md` file will be written in the work unit directory containing the specific failure reasons.

To resolve:
1. Read `.gate-feedback.md` in the work unit directory for the specific failures
2. Address each `[FAIL]` item — these are the blocking issues
3. Review any `[WARN]` items — these are advisory but may indicate quality gaps
4. Re-run the gate after fixes: `bash gates/advance.sh <unit-dir> <transition>`

The feedback file is deleted automatically on the next successful gate pass.
